    "section": "Question 4",
    "text": "Question 4\n\nset.seed(1234)\n\n\nrandom_vectors_list &lt;- as.list(irnorm(5, count = 3))#  iterator output to  list \n\n# Register a parallel backend \nnum_cores &lt;- parallel::detectCores(logical = FALSE)\nif (num_cores &gt; 1) {\n  cl &lt;- makeCluster(min(2, num_cores))  # Use up to 2 cores\n  registerDoParallel(cl)\n} else {\n  registerDoSEQ() \n}\n\n# Use foreach \nresults &lt;- foreach(v = random_vectors_list, .combine = c) %dopar% {\n  max(v)\n}\n\n# Stop the parallel cluster\nif (exists(\"cl\")) stopCluster(cl)\n\nresults\n\n[1] 1.0844412 0.5060559 0.9594941"
  },
  {
    "objectID": "Assignment2.html#question-6",
    "href": "Assignment2.html#question-6",
    "title": "Assignment2",
    "section": "Question 6",
    "text": "Question 6\n\nset.seed(1234)\n\nrandom_vectors_list &lt;- as.list(replicate(3, rnorm(5), simplify = FALSE))# Generate random vectors\n\n\nnum_cores &lt;- detectCores(logical = FALSE)# Register parallel backend\ncl &lt;- makeCluster(min(2, num_cores))\nregisterDoParallel(cl)\n\n\nsystem.time({\n  res_parLapply &lt;- parLapply(cl, random_vectors_list, max)  # parLapply\n})\n\n   user  system elapsed \n      0       0       0 \n\nsystem.time({\n  result_foreach &lt;- foreach(v = random_vectors_list, .combine = c) %dopar% { #Using foreach with %dopar%\n    Sys.sleep(0.001)\n    max(v)\n  }\n})\n\n   user  system elapsed \n   0.02    0.00    0.05 \n\n# Using replicate\nsystem.time({\n  result_replicate &lt;- sapply(random_vectors_list, max)\n})\n\n   user  system elapsed \n      0       0       0 \n\n# Stop the cluster\nstopCluster(cl)"
  }
